Calmodulin (CaM) facts and ﬁgures

9

• 16-18 kD (depending on species), ~20 x 40 Å protein
• highly conserved among eukaryotes (vertebrate and yeast calmodulin
are functionally interchangeable)
• binds four Ca2+ ions using EF hand amino acid sequence motifs
• Ca2+-CaM binds short segments of target proteins, modulates activity

